modules.description: Provides functions to initialize, query, and manage hardware performance counters, including starting and stopping events, reading counter values, and handling error conditions. Works with event identifiers, counter values, and configuration parameters specific to PAPI's interface. Used to monitor CPU cycles, cache misses, and other low-level performance metrics in high-performance computing applications.

This module offers low-level control over hardware performance counters through initialization, event management, and counter reading, operating on structures like event sets, event types, and error states. It enables precise performance monitoring for tasks such as application profiling and optimization, with examples demonstrating its use in tracking system-level metrics via PAPI's C library integration.
